data.description: Welcome to 703 S Magnolia St located in the beautiful Historic District of Summerville SC. Imagine walking to the Flowertown Festival in the Spring, walking to SHS football games on Fall Friday nights, or biking/golf carting to the quaint shops, spas and local restaurants downtown Summerville offers plus events like 3rd Thursdays on the square! This newly updated custom built 4 bed/3.5 bath home offers a flexible floorplan and is perfect for entertaining.  It features stunning hardwood floors, a large sunroom with office/study built-ins, a huge partially covered deck w/sink area, fans and lights, a mother-in-law suite/second primary bedroom/teenager retreat upstairs, plus a bonus room that could be a 5th bedroom. There is also a detached workshop with electric and water. When youarrive at this home, you will notice the long driveway and welcoming true full front porch complete with 2 porch swings and rocking chairs- all you need to do is bring the sweet tea! Upon entering you will notice the newly refinished and stained hardwood floors throughout most of the living areas, a freshly painted interior and custom dentil molding and chair rail in foyer, formal dining room and guest bedroom. Double doors lead to a large family room with a gas fireplace, tile hearth and surround, chair rail and crown molding. The large kitchen features custom built cabinets including a "secret" custom pantry, crown molding and granite counters with a tile backsplash, cooktop, wall oven plus a bay window breakfast area. Step down into the spacious sunroom with tile flooring that could be another family room/flex space/office. The 3 bedrooms downstairs including the primary bedroom are all generously sized and offer hardwood flooring and crown molding. The primary bedroom has 2 closets, and the walk-in has built-in shelving. The ensuite bath has a new double vanity with quartz counter, new mirrors, lighting and built-in shelving in water area. The hall bath features a new double vanity with quartz counter, new tile flooring, new mirror and new lighting. The laundry room has built-in shelving and cabinets for plenty of storage and the 1/2 bath has granite counters. Going upstairs you will find a newly updated bonus room with new LVP flooring and a closet which could be a 5th bedroom, playroom, media room, etc. Next you will see a large 4th bedroom with new carpet and a full bath with new LVP flooring-this area has so many possibilities. While upstairs, don't miss all the storage areas and the fabulous walk-in attic! The attached 2 car garage has cabinets, back entry door and water hook-up for a refrigerator. If you are looking for storage and a versatile floorplan, this home has it.      Going outside, you will see a huge deck with a covered area perfect for entertaining large gatherings. It features 3 ceiling fans, special railing lights and a sink area great for gardening or perfect for grilling prep. The detached building in the backyard is currently used as a workshop. Plantings include azaleas, hydrangeas, camellias and gardenias.                So, you don't have to imagine anymore - if you are looking for a great home in Historic Summerville close to Historic Downtown Summerville, Azalea Park, the Summerville Farmers Market and within walking distance to an elementary school, this is it!
